body.name: Giniros Mens Slip On Walking Shoes Non Slip Running Shoes Breathable Workout Shoes Lightweight Gym Sneakers
features: New lace up design and comfortable inner: The shoelaces are mainly used as decorations, making the shoes look more beautiful. And you will no longer need to lace up your shoes every time. Also, if you want your shoes to be more tightly fastened, you can adjust the tightness. The soft and smooth inner layer makes the shoes comfortable with or without socks, so they can be used as causal shoes.

Lightweight and soft sneakers: The breathable mesh uppers and synthetic soles are very lightweight, making you feel you're walking on clouds. And the insoles are soft, allowing you to stand for a long time without feeling tired. It is very suitable as Men's Walking Shoes, Athletic Shoes or Work Shoes.

Breathable and lightweight knitted upper: There are thousands of ventilation holes on the knitted upper to make it possible that your feet breathe freely, keeping your feet cool, clean and dry. And the knitted mesh fabric also can reduce sweating and prevent foot odor effectively when you run or walk.

Non-slip and durable soles: The synthetic sole is lightweight and it has good shock absorption, resilience, flexibility and impact resistance. The grooves in the outsole increase the slip-resistance and wear-resistance, and ensure the stability when walking. Because of these advantages, the shoes can adapt to a variety of climate and environment.

Occasion: The shoes come in many colors and you can match them with different clothes. These shoes are suitable for any daily life, such as: long time standing work, walking, jogging, running, riding, hiking, nursing, fishing, shopping, traveling, driving, indoor, outdoor and exercise etc.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on January 28, 2024
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Great Pair of Work Shoes!
reviews.reviewText: These shoes were originally intended as a cheap pair of work shoes that could get dirty; however, once they arrived, I fell in love. They fit perfectly, were extremely comfortable despite my expectations, and seem very durable. I did end up wearing them to work for about a week but had to end up buying a second pair which I used for daily/personal use. They are easy to clean and maintain and are as durable and comfortable as much as they are attractive! Will continue to purchase these shoes as the price seems like a steal for what you get! Thank you!!!

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on February 10, 2024
reviews.reviewText: I tear shoes up fast and frequent, seemingly regardless of brand, make or price. Maybe I'm doing something wrong there but either way it results in me ordering shoes frequently and I settle for something fairly low priced and I hope that it's comfortable enough to walk around in. These fit that perfectly. Maybe a half size too big which is what it is, they are comfortable and lightweight, black with minimal design so they aren't flashy. Wear with anything and you're good. Probably not good in rain but most running shoes aren't unless they're specifically designed for it. The downside to my personal situation is the good shoes I find don't tend to stay around when the current ones break down. Considering buying a 2nd pair for the future to avoid that issue

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on January 11, 2024
reviews.reviewText: A great looking shoe, the dark army green color looks so good and stylish with a masculine edge. I bought these for my husband and he really likes them. He says they are slightly above average in comfortability. Meaning it’s easy to wear them out for an event or running a few errands but as far as wearing them all day for work (where he’s on his feet walking the whole day) he prefers a different shoe that I also purchased on Amazon.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on February 8, 2024
reviews.reviewText: I really like these shoes. Comfy, easy on and off. Might get a second color too.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on January 8, 2024
reviews.reviewTitle: 3.0 out of 5 stars Soles slip and wear out
reviews.reviewText: I like the upper shoe. Flexible and breathable. Fit was a little too roomy but then again my feet are on the narrow side. My biggest complaint is the soles. They provide very poor traction so if you’ll be on damp grass or any slick surfaces it is not very secure. I rolled my ankles several times running before downgrading these to comfortable around-the-house shoes. But I wore them daily for about 6 weeks, maybe 50 miles (some road but most floor) and the soles were just worn down. Seems like a low density foam that is good for cushion and shock absorption but not good durability.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on January 30, 2024
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Keep up the good work
reviews.reviewText: Love this product they are very comfortable and affordable and they are also lightweight

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on December 24, 2023
reviews.reviewText: I was very pleasantly surprised. I was looking for a pair of dog walking shoes, I did not want to be bothered with laces but didn't feel like paying the price for Kiziks or Skechers. These came in and when I put them on for the first time, they felt very comfortable, lightweight material that surround my ankle and easy to slip on and off, just using the laces the first time to adjust the fit. For the price, these can't be beat and I am sure that when this pair wears out, I will come back for a second.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on December 9, 2023
reviews.reviewText: better than I expected at its price point. I will say there are a half size too big so go half size down and let you normally wear. I’ve always had a problem with skinny feet and these fit snug so that is a bonus for me. they’re super soft but, a bit plasticy.Overall, good choice at its price point. I do recommend ordering half a size lower than your normal size and it’s a great fit if you have skinny, long feet.
